<br>
The problem is, of course, the amount of healing done.  Whether it's team or solo doesn't matter.<br>
<br>
Healing aggro only seems to increase when healing the member being attacked.<br>
<br>
Since docs always get solo heals that do so many more points than team, they think 'solo heals aggro more!'.  In reality, if they find the team heal isn't aggroing, they should use the solo heal that heals the same amount, or maybe a touch more.  Otherwise they are burning nano for no reason (team heals take more nano to heal for N points than the solo that heals for N points - it's about HP - not spell QL).<br>
<br>
